<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=102977119670948></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102977119670948><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6806&mid=102977119670948>Random, maybe helpful, thoughts...</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6806&mid=102977119670948#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=96680><span id= >Lady Telora</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>14 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 19th 11:45 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just got one Saturday.&nbsp;&nbsp;Dropped off a Di'Zok Underling, we were pulling everything around Zone-in.  This seems to have a low drop rate, as we only got 1 in about 3 hours of killing.  We also got 1 SBS, so the poster who said it drops about as often was, in my experience, correct.<br><br>And from what I've been told by LOTS of people, is that the amount of mana you get is dependant on Character lvl and wis/int.  The formulas are:<br><br>For Wis/Int under 200: (lvl/10)*2<br>For Wis/Int over 200: lvl/10<br><br>Those may not be 100% accurate, but I hit the exact numbers Magelo gives me.<br><br>But anyway, using those formulas  if you have &gt;200 Wis, and are about lvl 50, then you are actually gaining 10 mana by swapping this ring for a Velium Jasper (+7 wis) ring.  Plus the extra 5hp, and saves are nice. (and yes, 5hp CAN be a life saver, after putting this ring on, I zoned into Umbral Planes on a bad pull with 1hp left...)  You may say &quot;Wow, a whole 10 mana!&quot;  But 10 mana may mean the difference between life and death for you tank.  Taking that extra tick to med that 10 mana may be more time than your tank has.  Yeah, it isn't much, but as some one said earlier... Every little bit helps!<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Oct  3 15:43:48 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
